arChildNodes.szComment: Jiona says lacuni arrived and ambushed her when she was without a weapon, frustred with herself.
Jiona describes the sudden appearance of a cloud that set upon the attacking lacuni
Jiona recalls being blinded by the cloud, but hearing terrible noises within.
Jiona speaks to the cloud dispursing suddenly, (unspoken) revealing the corpses of the lacuni who tried to ambush her.
Jiona questions the player, realising that her father went through with his ritual for Nyamoyo--to protect her.
Jiona says she can feel her father by her side, protecting her, even though he is gone.
Warmed by the through of his presence, Jiona gives her final thanks to her father.
